<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:39:15 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>揭示游走心灵的具体维度</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/uncovering-the-embodied-dimension-of-the-wandering-mind</link><description>休息时，大脑会全神贯注于自我产生的想法，通常称为走神。虽然这些思想的社会性、自传性和时间性特征已被广泛研究，但人们对游离的思想转向内感受体和躯体的频率知之甚少。为了绘制“ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/uncovering-the-embodied-dimension-of-the-wandering-mind3.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:39:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/uncovering-the-embodied-dimension-of-the-wandering-mind</guid></item><item><title>血栓切除术后连续灌注 MRI 无复流现象的时间动态</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/temporal-dynamics-of-the-no-reflow-phenomenon-on-serial-perfusion-mri-after-thrombectomy</link><description>现已上线！ COPII 货物识别对 STING 信号进行调节：Lyu 等人。鉴定 STING-ER-exit 基序及其被 COPII 囊泡货物结合蛋白 SEC24C 识别的机制。这项研究揭示了 STING 如何实现受控而非组成型 ER 退出，以及如何调节 STING 的 COPII 货物识别来控制 STING 信号传导。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/temporal-dynamics-of-the-no-reflow-phenomenon-on-serial-perfusion-mri-after-thrombectomy2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:24:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/temporal-dynamics-of-the-no-reflow-phenomenon-on-serial-perfusion-mri-after-thrombectomy</guid></item><item><title>联会复合体的结构和功能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/structure-and-function-of-the-synaptonemal-complex</link><description>Cesar 和 Kim 回顾了联会复合体如何组装并充当协调减数分裂重组的动态信号平台。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/structure-and-function-of-the-synaptonemal-complex.gif" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:09:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/structure-and-function-of-the-synaptonemal-complex</guid></item><item><title>过度使用智能手机的习惯与大脑情绪失调有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/excessive-smartphone-habits-tied-to-emotional-dysregulation-in-the-brain</link><description>一项新发布的神经影像学研究表明，过度使用智能手机的年轻人的杏仁核功能连接发生了改变。这些特定的神经差异与日常管理负面情绪的困难相关。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/excessive-smartphone-habits-tied-to-emotional-dysregulation-in-the-brain2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:54:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/excessive-smartphone-habits-tied-to-emotional-dysregulation-in-the-brain</guid></item><item><title>衰老的大脑会发生什么变化？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/what-changes-happen-in-the-aging-brain</link><description>索尔克研究所的一项新研究描绘了衰老的大脑如何在表观遗传水平上发生变化——逐个细胞类型。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/what-changes-happen-in-the-aging-brain.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:39:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/what-changes-happen-in-the-aging-brain</guid></item><item><title>中微子打破冰层</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neutrinos-make-a-break-in-the-ice</link><description>宇宙中微子的光谱可以揭示产生这些和其他高能粒子的天体物理源的类型。冰立方中微子观测站的探测器埋在南极冰层中，自 2010 年以来一直在测量宇宙中微子。早期发布的数据表明，中微子光谱是单一的下降幂律，这与宇宙中微子与宇宙射线相关的简单模型一致。但现在，经过 14 年的观察，IceCube 的数据显示，在能量约为 30 兆电子伏的光谱中存在断裂或膝状向下弯曲的证据。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/neutrinos-make-a-break-in-the-ice.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:24:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/neutrinos-make-a-break-in-the-ice</guid></item><item><title>阐明宇宙射线膝盖</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/elucidating-the-cosmic-ray-knee</link><description>对区分氢和氦的宇宙射线的新观察发现，长期观察的光谱特征具有意想不到的复杂性。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/elucidating-the-cosmic-ray-knee.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:09:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/elucidating-the-cosmic-ray-knee</guid></item><item><title>从工程真菌分子到先导药物，化学-生物混合合成使抗寄生虫药物的发现成为可能</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/from-engineered-fungal-molecules-to-drug-leads-chem-bio-hybrid-synthesis-enables-antiparasitic-drug-discovery</link><description>阿米巴病是一种由微小原生动物溶组织内阿米巴引起的寄生虫病。感染是通过摄入受污染的水或食物中的包囊而发生的。全球每年估计约有 5000 万有症状病例，主要发生在热带和亚热带地区。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/from-engineered-fungal-molecules-to-drug-leads-chem-bio-hybrid-synthesis-enables-antiparasitic-drug-discovery.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 10:54:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/from-engineered-fungal-molecules-to-drug-leads-chem-bio-hybrid-synthesis-enables-antiparasitic-drug-discovery</guid></item><item><title>场镜揭示 15 nm 氧化铟锡纳米晶体中的飞秒光学开关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/fieldoscopy-reveals-femtosecond-optical-switching-in-15-nm-indium-tin-oxide-nanocrystals</link><description>正如天线与无线电波相互作用一样，光与金属纳米结构相互作用。因此，了解结构如何影响场振荡可以为了解结构的物理特性提供有价值的见解。包括马克斯·普朗克光科学研究所 (MPL) 科学家在内的一个国际研究小组正在研究光与氧化铟锡 (ITO) 纳米晶体相互作用时发生的场振荡变化。这将加深我们对光与这些纳米晶体之间的相互作用如何取决于时间的理解。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/fieldoscopy-reveals-femtosecond-optical-switching-in-15-nm-indium-tin-oxide-nanocrystals.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 10:39:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/fieldoscopy-reveals-femtosecond-optical-switching-in-15-nm-indium-tin-oxide-nanocrystals</guid></item><item><title>新颖的测量证实了 50 年前的预测：暗点比光快</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/novel-measurement-confirms-a-50-year-old-prediction-dark-points-are-faster-than-light</link><description>以色列理工学院的一个研究小组&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/novel-measurement-confirms-a-50-year-old-prediction-dark-points-are-faster-than-light.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 10:24:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/03/novel-measurement-confirms-a-50-year-old-prediction-dark-points-are-faster-than-light</guid></item></channel></rss>